ographie und die spannungsreichen Zeitläufte der Jahre 1892-1917. Sie sind das Zeugnis eines virtuosen Briefschreibers, der schon als junger Mensch mit wichtigen Zeitgenossen korrespondierte: mit Politikern, Publizisten, Schriftstellern und Künstlern.  aThe years leading up to World War I were very influential for Theodor Heuss' development. As a school pupil in Heilbronn, a student in Munich and Berlin, and an editor in Berlin and Heilbronn, he made experiences that were to prove decisive for his later career. Besides politics he was also especially involved in the fields of visual art, literature and journalism. He continually advocated a radical departure from the German Kaiser Reich, perceiving it as authoritarian, and was farsighted in his later comments on the disaster of World War I.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aThis eBook is made available Open Access under a FA license: uhttps://www.degruyter.com/dg/page/free-access-policy uhttps://www.degruyter.com/dg/page/open-access-policy  aIn German.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 29. Nov 2021) 4aBrief/Sammlung. 4aDeutsches Kaiserreich. 4aHeuss, Theodor. 7aHISTORY / Europe / Germany.2bisacsh1 aBecker, Ernst Wolfgang, eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt1 aGünther, Frieder, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aGünther, Frieder, eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertDGBA History 2000 - 2014z9783110635836oZDB-23-GHI08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertE-BOOK GESAMTPAKET / COMPLETE PACKAGE 2009z9783110219517oZDB-23-DGG08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertE-BOOK PAKET PHILOSOPHIE UND GESCHICHTE 2009z9783110219500oZDB-23-DGE0 cprintz978359825123840uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/9783598441363zOpen Access7040uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9783598441363zOpen Access